                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-1003" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1003" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1003" type="surname" value="SPICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1003" type="given" value="ALFERD"></interp>ALFERD SPICE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, V</hi> 47). On 21st Nov., about twenty minutes past seven o'clock, I stopped the prisoner near the Swan at Stockwell, carry<lb></lb>in something heavy, I asked what he had got, he said some lead—I asked where he got it—he said he found it on Clapham-common—I said he must go to the station—I took it from him, and one piece from his trowsers, and another from his jacket at the station—it weighed 13lbs.—on 23rd I received information, took it to Mr. Thornton's, Clapham-common, and compared it with two pieces on the fowl-house—it corresponded, and had been recently cut—I found two knives in his pocket with a lead mark on the edge of one.</p>
               <p>
